<h1>Game Decisions - Settings</h1>
<h2>FLEEING THE CITY:</h2>
  Choices to flee the city vary based on socioeconomic class, family size, place of origin, and whether you are the head of household. DAY LABORERS have an additional choice: they can choose to follow their masters or break from their master's choice.
 <ul>
    <li>Single players who are also head of household (i.e., not a child) will have the choice to remain in the city with their household, remain in the city alone and send away their family, or flee with their household.</li>
    or flee the city.
    <li>
  
    <ul><li>1: Stay with your master </li>
    <li>2: Flee with your master (no reputation hit, no income hit)</li>
    <li>3: Flee without your master: you abandon your duties and take a reputation/income hit.</li>
    <li>4: Stay with your household</li>
    <li>5: Stay but send your household away</li>
    <li>6: Flee with your household</li>
    <li>7: You attempt to flee but can't due to lack of funds.
      </ul>

  <h1>Game settings</h1>
    HOH 0 = not head of household
    HOH 1 = head of household
